{{Infobox person |name = Angad Paul |image = Angad Paul, Chief Executive Officer, Caparo Industries, United Kingdom, Horasis Annual Meeting 2013 (8437967120).jpg |image_size = |caption = Angad Paul, January 2013 |birth_name = |birth_date = {{birth date|1970|6|6|df=y}} |birth_place = London, England |death_date = {{Death date and age|2015|11|8|1970|6|6|df=y}} |death_place = London, England |residence = |nationality = British |ethnicity = |citizenship = |other_names = |known_for = |education = |alma_mater = [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] |occupation = CEO, [[Caparo plc]] |years_active = |home_town = |salary = |networth = |title = |term = |predecessor = |successor = |boards = |spouse = Michelle Bonn |children = |parents = [[Swraj Paul, Baron Paul]] |relations = |website = }}
'''Angad Paul''' (6 June 1970 – 8 November 2015) was a British businessman and [[film producer]].
==Background and education== He was born on 6 June 1970,<ref name=Indobit>{{cite news|last1=Williamson|first1=Marcus|authorlink1=Marcus Williamson|title=Angad Paul: Head of the Caparo steel empire who also helped fund such films as 'Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels'|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/angad-paul-head-of-the-caparo-steel-empire-who-also-helped-fund-such-films-as-lock-stock-and-two-a6727786.html|accessdate=10 November 2015|work=The Independent|date=10 November 2015}}</ref> the youngest son of the billionaire entrepreneur and politician [[Swraj Paul, Baron Paul]].<ref name=Guardian /> He attended [[Harrow School]] and received a degree in economics from the [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]].<ref name=Guardian /><ref name=Indobit/>
==Career== He was [[CEO]] of [[Caparo|Caparo Industries]], having taken over from his father in 1996. He also produced films, including <ref name=Guardian /> ''[[Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels]]'', ''[[Snatch (film)|Snatch]]'',<ref name="Caparo boss"> {{cite news | url= https://www.bbc.com/news/business-34765572 | title= Caparo boss Angad Paul dies after falling from penthouse flat | publisher= [[BBC News]] }} </ref> and ''[[The Tournament (2009 film)|The Tournament]]''.
==Personal life== In March 2005, Paul was married to media lawyer Michelle Bonn in a ceremony held at [[Lancaster House]].<ref name=TelegraphWedding>{{cite news|first1=Amit|last1=Roy|title=Lord Paul hosts wedding party to outdo Versailles spectacular|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1485990/Lord-Paul-hosts-wedding-party-to-outdo-Versailles-spectacular.html|accessdate=10 November 2015|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=19 March 2005}}</ref> They had two children.<ref name=Guardian>{{cite news|title=Caparo steel boss Angad Paul dies after falling from London flat|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/nov/09/caparo-steel-boss-angad-paul-dies-falling-london-flat|accessdate=9 November 2015|work=The Guardian|date=9 November 2015}}</ref>
==Death== Paul died on 8 November 2015 after falling from his penthouse home, an eight-storey building in [[Portland Place]], [[central London]].<ref name=Telegraph>{{cite news|last1=Ward|first1=Victoria|title=Son of Lord Paul, the billionaire steel magnate, plunges to his death as the family business collapses|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/law-and-order/11983254/Son-of-Lord-Paul-the-billionaire-steel-magnate-plunges-to-his-death-as-the-family-business-collapses.html|accessdate=9 November 2015|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=9 November 2015}}</ref> The police stated that there were no suspicious circumstances.<ref name=Guardian />
