{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Use Australian English|date=April 2018}} {{Infobox rugby league biography |name = Roy Algie |fullname = Leslie Roy Algie |birth_date = 1889 |birth_place = [[Glebe, New South Wales]] |death_date = 24 January 1946 |death_place = Fivedock [[New South Wales]] |retired = yes |position = {{rlp|FB}} |club1 = [[Glebe (rugby league team)|Glebe]] |year1start = 1910 |year1end = 1914 |appearances1 = 52 |tries1 = 39 |goals1 = 52 |fieldgoals1 = 3 |points1 = 227
}} '''Leslie Roy 'Bunny' Algie''' (1889-1946) was an Australian rugby league player from the 1910s.
Born at [[Glebe, New South Wales]] in 1889, Roy Algie played full-back for the [[Glebe (rugby league team)|Glebe Dirty Reds]] between 1910-1914. He played 55 first grade games for Glebe and was a prolific point scorer. 'Bunny' Algie scored 24 tries, 28 goals and 3 field goals (total 134 points) during his career at Glebe. He was also the [[NSWRFL]] season top try scorer in 1912.
Algie finished his career at the [[Balmain Tigers]], playing one season in 1916.<ref>Alan Whiticker/Glen Hudson: Encyclopedia of Rugby League Players. 1995 ({{ISBN|1875169571}})</ref>
Roy Algie died on 24 January 1946, aged 55.<ref>Sydney Morning Herald: Death Notice 26/1/1946</ref>
